ations previously.     More specifically the successful applicant would have:- Experience bunker tanker operation, fuel supply logistic, terminal operation, fuel quality and operational safety. Managed operational matters regarding the supply of heavy fuel oil. Experience in Barge operations and Risk management where successfully have been able to fix costs. Managed a diverse team of operators in various locations in Asia Pacific region. Managed external contractors/operators (terminals, truck, bunker tanker).  Assisted in new physical operational development and have a track record of optimising both commercial and operational requirements. It will be an added advantage if you have bunkering, shipping, terminal operation or cargo trading experience.  Fuel trading or barge operational experience will also be an advantage.     You will have to be willing to do business travel required will be required(around 20% of the year)   Your soft sills will allow you to work in a structured organisation, be pro-active both approach internally and externally and able to communicate efficiently over the phone in English and Mandarin. You will need to be culturally aware and resolve issues. You will also be a team player, good communication skills and the ability to remain calm and objective under pressure.   JOB DESCRIPTION The role has 3 elements i.e. Commercial, Operational and Quality & Safety.   Commercial Cooperation with traders/sales team. Participate in customer / supplier meetings. Optimise logistic supply chain. Operation cost budgeting.  Operation Manage a team of operators to deliver top class product and service to customers. Manage external contractors to deliver top class product and service. Cargo resupply and optimisation planning.  Quality & Safety Health and Safety accountability. Manage fuel quality (ISO 8217 fuel quality knowledge). Safe operation.  REMUNERATION PACKAGE An exceptional package and performance bonus is on offer.About this companyRed The Consul